data.description: Two levels with two-car carport with detached storage shed on fully-cemented back patio.  Patio space for outside table and grill which is great in the warm seasons.  Upstairs has very open floor plan between living and dining rooms with roomy bedrooms (master bedroom on the first floor is same size as downstairs bedroom).  Downstairs family/rec room with 2 bedrooms.  Good as a playroom and the bedrooms are perfect for older children.  Downstairs is mostly below ground so tends to be well insulated--cool in the summer and warm in the winter.  Majority of downstairs is finished with approximately 360 sq. ft. of unfinished space where laundry.  Great as a workshop or storage.
data.whatILove: Great neighborhood if you have young kids.  Literally across the street from Sharon Park and Sharon Park elementary school (parents "take" their kids to school by standing on the front porch and just making sure they cross the street fine.  super easy).  Quick and easy access to the park, which is always full of families on the weekends and is quiet at night.  Park is fun during all seasons because there's a small hill for sledding for smaller children and two separate playgrounds for other seasons.  Lots of room to run around and good for pets too.  This is a neighborhood two blocks from the Catholic church which frequently has festivals and other community events during the year.  The general vicinity is a mix of Caucasian and Hispanic/Latino homeowners and most neighbors love the added diversity in an otherwise homogeneous city.  Everyone is friendly and the area is safe.  HOA also covers all maintenance (snow removal, sprinkler repair, landscaping, etc.).
